          <text><![CDATA[<p> <b>Opioid Immediate Suspension Order Act of 2017</b></p> <p>This bill amends the Controlled Substances Act to eliminate the provision that defines the phrase &quot;imminent danger to the public health and safety.&quot; Under current law, the Drug Enforcement Administration may immediately suspend the registration of a controlled substances manufacturer, distributor, or dispenser to prevent imminent danger to the public health and safety.</p>]]></text>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <actionDate>2017-10-16</actionDate>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <updateDate>2017-10-16T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
    </summaries>
